 ── Why AGPL-3.0 for the core daemon? ──
 The core daemon is licensed under AGPL-3.0 to protect against cloud resellers
 (e.g. AWS, Amazon, Twitch itself) taking the code, hosting it as a SaaS, and
 capturing all the value without contributing back. Under AGPL-3.0, anyone who
 modifies engelOS and offers it as a network service must release their
 modifications under the same license.

 ── What is NOT AGPL? ──
 - The SDK (pkg/sdk/) is licensed under Apache-2.0 so that tool vendors like
   Elgato, Razer, or independent developers can build integrations without
   their work being captured by AGPL. See pkg/sdk/LICENSE.
 - The Cloud features (not in this repo, hosted at engelos.com) are proprietary.

 ── For end users ──
 You can:
 - Use engelOS for any purpose, including commercial streaming
 - Modify it
 - Self-host it on your own server or PC
 - Distribute modified versions

 You must:
 - Keep the source available if you offer the modified version as a network
   service (this is the "Affero" clause)
 - Preserve copyright notices

